        <trans-unit id="102" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>How to: Animate the Color or Opacity of a SolidColorBrush</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>This example shows how to animate the              <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.SolidColorBrush.Color%2A&gt;</ph> and              <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.Brush.Opacity%2A&gt;</ph> of a              <ph id="ph3">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.SolidColorBrush&gt;</ph>.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Example</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The following example uses three animations to animate the                      <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.SolidColorBrush.Color%2A&gt;</ph> and                      <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.Brush.Opacity%2A&gt;</ph> of a                      <ph id="ph3">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.SolidColorBrush&gt;</ph>.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The first animation, a                              <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.ColorAnimation&gt;</ph>, changes the brush's color to                              <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.Colors.Gray%2A&gt;</ph> when the mouse enters the rectangle.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The next animation, another                              <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.ColorAnimation&gt;</ph>, changes the brush's color to                              <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.Colors.Orange%2A&gt;</ph> when the mouse leaves the rectangle.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The final animation, a                              <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.DoubleAnimation&gt;</ph>, changes the brush's opacity to 0.0 when the left mouse button is pressed.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
